    "title": "crash when closing bitcoind with -detachdb=1",
    "body": "I am running the binaries provided by gaven for 0.7.2rc2.\n\nI started bitcoind with -detachdb=1 just to test whether everything was working well.  On first attempt I got:\n\nmike@alpha:~$ ~/bitcoin-0.7.2/bitcoin-0.7.2rc2-linux/bin/32/bitcoind -detachdb=1\n<pressed CTRL+C>\nterminate called after throwing an instance of 'boost::exception_detail::clone_implboost::exception_detail::error_info_injector<boost::system::system_error >'\n  what():  mutex: Invalid argument\nAborted\n\nI think started again with detachdb=1 and everything seemed fine.  I shut down and no issues.  I started again and everything fine and shut down with no issues.  So this happened once and I can't get it to happen again.  I am using 32-bit debian.\n",
